It was the day after
we quit therapy.

256
00:10:39,272 --> 00:10:41,906
And I met her at the hospital.

257
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:55,186
Yeah. We're fine.

258
00:10:59,592 --> 00:11:00,592
We're fine.

259
00:11:00,644 --> 00:11:02,259
I should be your person!

260
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,411
<i>Be my person!</i>

261
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:06,748
Be my person, Owen!
Be my freaking person!

262
00:11:08,969 --> 00:11:10,368
Be my person.

263
00:11:12,456 --> 00:11:14,989
29-year-old female.
MVC collision with a truck.

264
00:11:15,058 --> 00:11:16,624
Take her to trauma one.

265
00:11:16,693 --> 00:11:19,461
Hypotensive in the field. She
received two liters LR en route.

266
00:11:19,529 --> 00:11:22,430
Okay, let's get trauma labs
and set up for an ultrasound.

267
00:11:22,499 --> 00:11:23,743
All right. I'll check it.

268
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:24,899
Is anybody with her?

269
00:11:25,535 --> 00:11:26,634
I am.

270
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:45,419
What was her name?

271
00:11:49,358 --> 00:11:51,092
Honestly? I...

272
00:11:52,328 --> 00:11:53,961
I don't remember.

273
00:11:55,698 --> 00:11:57,131
He's in the car.

274
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,767
Chief.

275
00:11:59,836 --> 00:12:02,198
See, from 1:00 to 2:00, you
have "Lunch with the Chief."

276
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:04,189
I told you to call it
"Beef with the Chief."

277
00:12:04,257 --> 00:12:05,623
It's got a ring to it.

278
00:12:05,692 --> 00:12:07,592
You got a beef, come
meet with the Chief.

279
00:12:07,660 --> 00:12:09,888
I didn't realize you
were serious about that.

280
00:12:09,912 --> 00:12:12,090
You need to let people get
the little things off their chests

281
00:12:12,114 --> 00:12:14,014
before they become big things.

282
00:12:14,083 --> 00:12:15,916
I'm serious about
this Chief thing, Avery.

283
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,446
It's my shot. I
want to do it right.

284
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:20,020
"Beef with the Chief," put
it in the schedule tomorrow.

285
00:12:22,192 --> 00:12:24,170
Dr. Shepherd, Dr. Warren.

286
00:12:24,194 --> 00:12:25,271
Here.

287
00:12:25,295 --> 00:12:27,039
Mr. Cooper. How are you feeling?

288
00:12:27,063 --> 00:12:29,408
Like I would kill my own
mother for a burger and a shake.

289
00:12:29,432 --> 00:12:30,615
Jason Cooper,

290
00:12:30,683 --> 00:12:33,496
29-year-old male with
advanced juvenile arthritis,

291
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,320
causing fusion of the jaw

292
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:38,083
and extensive fusion of
the C2, C3 and C4 vertebrae.

293
00:12:38,107 --> 00:12:39,952
He's been on a feeding
tube for the past eight months.

294
00:12:39,976 --> 00:12:41,376
No solid food at all.

295
00:12:41,444 --> 00:12:43,277
Don't worry, Mr. Cooper.

296
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:44,996
After we break your jaw

297
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,910
and put in those sweet
titanium hinges I made for you,

298
00:12:47,934 --> 00:12:50,601
you'll be eating
burgers again real soon.

299
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:52,314
Could we have a word
with you outside, please?

300
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:53,604
Of course.

301
00:12:53,673 --> 00:12:55,100
Ben and I don't think we
should do the surgery today.

302
00:12:55,124 --> 00:12:56,707
Why not?

303
00:12:56,776 --> 00:12:58,220
With his cervical fusion, lying
him down on an operating table

304
00:12:58,244 --> 00:12:59,922
is gonna put pressure
on the base of his spine.

305
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:01,607
Not to mention that orotracheal

306
00:13:01,631 --> 00:13:03,275
intubation is
impossible on this guy.

307
00:13:03,299 --> 00:13:06,111
I'll do nasotracheal, but if
there's any compromise to the tube

308
00:13:06,135 --> 00:13:07,713
while he's under and
he's got no mobility...

309
00:13:07,737 --> 00:13:09,503
Let's just say, I can't
guarantee anything.

310
00:13:09,573 --> 00:13:11,021
What's your recommendation?

311
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:13,169
We postpone the surgery
until other plans can be made.

312
00:13:13,193 --> 00:13:15,154
And, Dr. Avery, what would
support performing the surgery

313
00:13:15,178 --> 00:13:17,078
as soon as possible?

314
00:13:17,146 --> 00:13:20,264
The patient has a major
abscess in the back of his mouth.

315
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,217
Which could lead to
sepsis or endocarditis.

316
00:13:23,286 --> 00:13:25,936
Infection's a killer, which
is why this can't wait.

317
00:13:26,006 --> 00:13:27,566
So let's figure out a way to get

318
00:13:27,590 --> 00:13:29,151
Mr. Cooper into
surgery on schedule.

319
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:31,053
Frankly, I don't know what
you think I can do for him

320
00:13:31,077 --> 00:13:32,310
by 3:00 this afternoon.

321
00:13:32,379 --> 00:13:33,856
Rise. Excuse me?

322
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,174
You have it in you.
Lost causes, right?

323
00:13:36,198 --> 00:13:38,649
Making the impossible possible?

324
00:13:38,718 --> 00:13:41,718
Rise to the challenge,
Shepherd. I believe in you.

325
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:44,004
Rise.

326
00:13:46,243 --> 00:13:47,591
All right, guys.

327
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:52,297
So you take orders
from Sloan now?

328
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:07,761
Hey! Where do you think
you're... You just can't take those.

329
00:14:07,848 --> 00:14:10,248
I was just gonna copy 'em
and bring 'em right back.

330
00:14:10,317 --> 00:14:11,666
It'll take two seconds.

331
00:14:11,735 --> 00:14:14,168
They don't teach you
about HIPAA in med school?

332
00:14:14,237 --> 00:14:16,937
You don't see a copy
machine, do you?

333
00:14:17,006 --> 00:14:18,906
That's because these
charts are private.

334
00:14:18,974 --> 00:14:22,576
They don't get copied and
they don't leave this room, ever.

335
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,646
Come on.

336
00:14:25,714 --> 00:14:28,394
I'm a fifth year. I'm just
trying to study for my boards.

337
00:14:28,418 --> 00:14:30,284
I need real cases. So read 'em.

338
00:14:30,353 --> 00:14:32,248
Read 'em all, but
they don't go outta here

339
00:14:32,272 --> 00:14:34,588
except in your
brain, understand?

340
00:14:36,426 --> 00:14:38,259
Yeah, I think I do.

341
00:14:39,345 --> 00:14:40,894
There you go.

342
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:43,864
Hey, you got a busy
schedule today?

343
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:45,265
Why?

344
00:14:45,335 --> 00:14:47,045
Do you need help
with that thyroidectomy?

345
00:14:47,069 --> 00:14:48,781
Because I've never done one,
and I was just reading about

346
00:14:48,805 --> 00:14:51,850
how it can sometimes cause
a thyroid storm, which is...

347
00:14:51,874 --> 00:14:52,985
How cool is that, you know?

348
00:14:53,009 --> 00:14:54,142
Yeah, maybe.

349
00:14:54,210 --> 00:14:57,845
Listen, your whole
photographic memory thing,

350
00:14:57,914 --> 00:14:59,864
how does that work?

351
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:02,500
You want me to memorize these?

352
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:03,601
Yeah.

353
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,397
All of them?
That'll take forever.

354
00:15:05,421 --> 00:15:06,703
Lexie, we need your help.

355
00:15:06,773 --> 00:15:09,384
We can't keep doing stupid
hypotheticals off index cards.

356
00:15:09,408 --> 00:15:11,453
We need someone to
question us off real cases.

357
00:15:11,477 --> 00:15:12,988
I have rounds. I have post-ops.

358
00:15:13,012 --> 00:15:16,230
Lexie, next year when
Karev and I are attendings,

359
00:15:16,298 --> 00:15:19,533
we will be assigning surgeries
and putting in our recommendations

360
00:15:19,602 --> 00:15:20,884
for chief resident.

361
00:15:20,954 --> 00:15:23,521
Are you sure you want to
get off on the wrong foot?

362
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,223
No.

363
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:26,557
No.

364
00:15:31,381 --> 00:15:32,847
Great!

365
00:15:32,916 --> 00:15:35,197
It is so much fun that you're
gonna be studying with us.

366
00:15:38,488 --> 00:15:40,332
You get to watch
the game tonight.

367
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:41,389
I do?

368
00:15:41,457 --> 00:15:43,536
I gotta go to some girls' night

369
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:46,093
Callie and Arizona
put together for Teddy.

370
00:15:47,062 --> 00:15:48,874
I mean, that's good, right?

371
00:15:48,898 --> 00:15:51,977
Wasn't I gonna get some
long story about how this is

372
00:15:52,001 --> 00:15:53,545
"the game of a lifetime,

373
00:15:53,569 --> 00:15:56,303
"and if you would just
sit still for five minutes,

374
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:58,350
"you might appreciate
the beauty of..."

375
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:01,192
You and I have been on
completely opposite schedules

376
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:03,127
for, like, two weeks.

377
00:16:03,196 --> 00:16:04,511
Tuck is at his dad's.

378
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:08,015
So I wasn't planning on
watching the game tonight.

379
00:16:08,617 --> 00:16:09,883
You weren't?

380
00:16:10,937 --> 00:16:12,620
Thank you, Doctor. Nope.

381
00:16:12,689 --> 00:16:14,049
What were you planning to do?

382
00:16:14,073 --> 00:16:15,217
I could say it out loud, but...

383
00:16:15,241 --> 00:16:16,674
Here you go.

384
00:16:16,742 --> 00:16:19,193
It would be inappropriate
for the workplace,

385
00:16:19,262 --> 00:16:20,844
so I'm just gonna think it.

386
00:16:28,337 --> 00:16:29,577
Oh...

387
00:16:38,681 --> 00:16:40,359
I'm gonna get
out of girls' night.

388
00:16:40,383 --> 00:16:41,383
Mmm-hmm.

389
00:16:43,619 --> 00:16:44,718
I got the donor scans.

390
00:16:44,787 --> 00:16:47,287
Great. Let's see what you got.

391
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:51,992
There.

392
00:16:53,796 --> 00:16:56,446
Bowel looks good, small
intestines, large intestines,

393
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,299
and that's a
good-looking pancreas.

394
00:16:58,367 --> 00:17:00,179
Look at that on
the liver right there.

395
00:17:00,203 --> 00:17:01,285
Looks like a tumor.

396
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:02,998
That makes him an
unsuitable organ donor.

397
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:06,139
Not necessarily. Could
be a benign adenoma.

398
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:08,170
My patient's been in
for two other transplants,

399
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:09,560
and they both fell through.

400
00:17:09,629 --> 00:17:11,173
He's not gonna live much
longer without a new liver.

401
00:17:11,197 --> 00:17:13,097
We could resect it.

402
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:16,033
It's a little unconventional
to operate on a donor,

403
00:17:16,102 --> 00:17:18,262
but there's no reason
why it wouldn't work.

404
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:20,371
That's a great idea, Bailey.

405
00:17:20,439 --> 00:17:21,767
Great idea? You want to put

406
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:24,575
compromised organs
into a transplant recipient

407
00:17:24,644 --> 00:17:26,855
and give your guy cancer
on top of everything else?

408
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:29,980
I think we owe it to my guy to at
least excise the tumor and test it.

409
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,250
I don't agree.

410
00:17:32,318 --> 00:17:36,670
Dr. Sloan, are you arguing
surgical protocol with Dr. Webber?

411
00:17:36,739 --> 00:17:38,506
Dr. Bailey,

412
00:17:38,574 --> 00:17:42,026
are you arguing with the
decision of the Chief of Surgery?

413
00:17:47,266 --> 00:17:48,582
Call UNOS.

414
00:17:48,651 --> 00:17:50,462
Tell them this
donor's unsuitable.

415
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,926
Put Mr. Sheridan
back on the list.

416
00:18:01,547 --> 00:18:04,115
We've put you back
on the transplant list.

417
00:18:04,183 --> 00:18:07,001
And a new set of organs
can come in at any time.

418
00:18:07,069 --> 00:18:10,003
Cut the crap, Dr. Webber.

419
00:18:10,072 --> 00:18:12,039
You and I both know
I'm not gonna make it

420
00:18:12,107 --> 00:18:17,495
to see the sunrise tomorrow,
let alone to stick around

421
00:18:17,564 --> 00:18:20,814
for some other poor,
sad sack to kick it.

422
00:18:20,883 --> 00:18:22,961
Mr. Sheridan, is there
anyone we can call for you,

423
00:18:22,985 --> 00:18:25,197
your family, your
sisters, your friends?

424
00:18:25,221 --> 00:18:27,087
Are you kidding?

425
00:18:27,156 --> 00:18:30,658
Thank God my family's
not around for this.

426
00:18:30,726 --> 00:18:34,578
It's like Lucy with a
football, except it's my life.

427
00:18:34,647 --> 00:18:37,481
It would kill them worse
than the first two times

428
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:39,650
to come in here and
say good-bye to me.

429
00:18:41,170 --> 00:18:44,489
We're all alone in
this world, sunshine.

430
00:18:44,557 --> 00:18:47,858
Anybody who tells
you any different is lying

431
00:18:47,927 --> 00:18:50,261
or trying to sell you something.

432
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:53,681
Now you...

433
00:18:53,749 --> 00:18:56,483
You are the best
doctor I ever had.

434
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:59,703
So don't beat
yourself up about this.

435
00:18:59,772 --> 00:19:01,772
It's done. It's over.

436
00:19:02,608 --> 00:19:04,591
You did everything you could.

437
00:19:06,346 --> 00:19:07,478
No.

438
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:09,875
No, I didn't.

439
00:19:09,899 --> 00:19:11,059
Sir.

440
00:19:11,100 --> 00:19:14,017
Bailey, your tumor
resection idea was sound.

441
00:19:14,086 --> 00:19:16,937
And there was no reason
why those organs wouldn't work.

442
00:19:18,224 --> 00:19:20,457
The donor is still
on life support.

443
00:19:20,526 --> 00:19:22,420
The organ recovery
for the heart and

444
00:19:22,444 --> 00:19:24,306
lungs isn't scheduled
till this afternoon.

445
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:25,474
But Dr. Sloan...

446
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:26,914
You let me deal
with Chief Sloan.

447
00:19:30,503 --> 00:19:34,221
When you're the Chief, you
gotta make the hard decisions.

448
00:19:34,289 --> 00:19:36,790
Webber knows that.
It comes with the job.

449
00:19:36,859 --> 00:19:38,299
Who's our first
appointment, Avery?

450
00:19:38,328 --> 00:19:39,988
No one on the schedule, Chief.

451
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,724
That's why you shoulda
called it "Beef with the Chief."

452
00:19:41,748 --> 00:19:43,388
People would've
shown up for that.

453
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,769
You got a beef?

454
00:19:48,838 --> 00:19:51,198
Actually, I would really love
to go study for my boards.

455
00:19:51,991 --> 00:19:52,991
No.

456
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,570
I know, I don't have
an appointment,

457
00:19:55,594 --> 00:19:56,872
but do you have a
moment to talk about

458
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:58,296
Jason Cooper's
jaw reconstruction?

459
00:19:58,364 --> 00:20:00,142
That's fine. He's wide
open. Have a seat.

460
00:20:00,166 --> 00:20:01,698
There you go.

461
00:20:01,767 --> 00:20:04,129
I think I can carve
out of foam a cradle

462
00:20:04,153 --> 00:20:05,664
that holds the patient's
head and neck during surgery,

463
00:20:05,688 --> 00:20:09,089
reducing the chance of
respiratory complication.

464
00:20:09,158 --> 00:20:10,641
That's a good idea.

465
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,220
But you can do
better. Excuse me?

466
00:20:12,244 --> 00:20:13,945
Foam's fine if
nothing goes wrong,

467
00:20:14,013 --> 00:20:15,591
but it won't be flexible enough

468
00:20:15,615 --> 00:20:17,142
if we have to adjust
him mid-surgery.

469
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,643
It's a good idea,
but... Are you aware...

470
00:20:18,667 --> 00:20:19,828
I'm aware... Of what?

471
00:20:19,852 --> 00:20:21,530
That that surgery is
taking place at 3:00,

472
00:20:21,554 --> 00:20:24,404
and Jason Cooper's
airway needs to be secured.

473
00:20:24,474 --> 00:20:26,574
So rise, Shepherd.

474
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:27,741
Rise.

475
00:20:30,396 --> 00:20:31,929
I can't do ladies' night.

476
00:20:31,997 --> 00:20:33,074
Sorry. What?

477
00:20:33,098 --> 00:20:34,331
But we need you.

478
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:38,052
I can't come
because Ben and I are

479
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:41,689
taking dance
lessons tonight, salsa.

480
00:20:43,309 --> 00:20:44,620
You and Ben... Yeah.

